Step 1: Identify the debt (liabilities) at the end of the period. Here, the liabilities are given as:
 • Accounts Payable = 247,000.00  
 • Taxes Payable = 131,850.51  
Total Liabilities = 247,000.00 + 131,850.51 = 378,850.51

Step 2: Obtain the Total Assets at the end of the period, which is given as:
 • Total Assets = 14,214,117.02

Step 3: Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio using the formula:
 Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets  
 = 378,850.51 / 14,214,117.02  
 ≈ 0.02665

Step 4: Rounding the ratio to two decimal places:
 ≈ 0.03

Thus, the Debt to Asset Ratio as of the end of the reporting period is approximately 0.03.
